name: tc.auroch
description: Auroch or the snow-camel are large horned cattle animals grown in large herds for their delicious meat and thick wool. Auroch-herding is especially common in the far north on the Katla isola, where their long long wool and general resilience make them perfect catle for harsh climate and demanding living conditions.

name: tc.kipt
description: *Kipt* is a pejorative term used to describe the dark skinned inhabitants of the Seminine islands. Linguists have traced the word back to "kiptoga", it's an umbrella term for the various bamboo boats the locals use to commute between the islands in the large archipelago.

name: tc.seraise_giant_hornet

name: tc.revachol_was_a_colony_of_surlaclef
description: In the very, very early days of colonizing this archipelago, the Kingdom of Suresne, a precursor of modern Sur-La-Clef, used to own the city of Revachol. An obscure detail in the bigger picture, but to some people it remains a point of contention to this day.

name: tc.daganagit
description: Daganagit is one of the smallest inhabited Seminine islands, located on the northern part of the archipelago and covered with thick lush jungle. Now mostly a favourite beach resort for the very richest who seek the *virgin* wilderness experience with subtle 5-star service, it used to be an anchor point for the Seminine resistance movement. The unusually lush plant-life on the island is often attributed to extensive use of napalm in the region during the early days of the Semenine conflict.
